
[1]rheumatism

   RHEU'MATISM, n. [L. rheumatismus; Gr. from a watery humor, from to
   flow; the ancients supposing the disease to proceed from a defluxion of
   humors.]

   A painful disease affecting muscles and joints of the human body,
   chiefly the larger joints, as the hips, knees, shoulders, &c.
